<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1095,1301]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1095,1120]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[276,590,1096,1120]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coeruleocephala" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[276,590,1096,1120]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Episcepsis coeruleocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[599,730,1095,1120]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[599,730,1095,1120]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
was described from an undetermined number of males. Only one was found at the 
<collectionCode box="[387,475,1133,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">BMNH</collectionCode>
. To our knowledge, this species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1100,1206,1132,1157]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
, which is why it was not possible to dissect it. The closest described species is 
<emphasis box="[835,980,1168,1192]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[835,976,1168,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moloneyi">E. moloneyi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which it differs externally in the forewing pattern: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[355,490,1204,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moloneyi">
<emphasis box="[355,490,1204,1228]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. moloneyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have the veins well marked in a darker hue of brown as it happens in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coeruleocephala" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. coeruleocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,494,1239,1264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[355,494,1239,1264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
On the other hand, the proximal area of hindwings is less marked in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coeruleocephala" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">E. coeruleocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[344,473,1276,1301]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[344,473,1276,1301]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
